\ array>cons / cons>array conversions. array>cons makes the last array element
\ the tail (same rule as the [( reader); cons>array derefs the spine and each
\ element and includes the terminal. Inverses for atom-element lists.
[ 1 2 3 ] array>cons . cr                      \ [( 1 2 3 )]
[ 1 2 3 ] array>cons cons>array . cr           \ [ 1 2 3 ]
[( 1 2 3 )] cons>array . cr                    \ [ 1 2 3 ]
[( 1 2 3 null )] cons>array . cr               \ [ 1 2 3 null ]
[ ] array>cons . cr                            \ null
[ 9 ] array>cons . cr                          \ 9
lvar to X  lvar to T  [( 5 6 )] [( X T )] ~ drop  [( X T )] cons>array . cr    \ [ 5 6 ]
bye
